  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/nagaraja-cou1-ortho-dr01",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-ortho-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors have been assessed and all achievedLevel values meet or exceed their requiredLevel. The FEA model of tibial tray micromotion has been validated against cadaveric and synthetic bone surrogate data with a quantitative validation metric (MAE 18 µm) well within the acceptance threshold (30 µm). Sensitivity analysis confirms that the dominant uncertainty contributors (cancellous bone modulus, friction coefficient) have been characterised and their combined effect bounded to ±25 µm, maintaining a margin of 125 µm against the 150 µm clinical threshold. The model operating envelope is fully defined and the validation domain overlaps the COU domain without unmitigated extrapolation. Software quality assurance, code verification, and discretization error are all at Gradation 3, appropriate for MRL 3. The package is assessed as credible to support the regulatory submission for the Class II cementless tibial tray.",
